    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "Then they that have kept God&apos;s commandments shall breathe in immortal vigor beneath the tree of life; and through unending ages the inhabitants of sinless worlds shall behold, in that garden of delight, a sample of the perfect work of God&apos;s creation, untouched by the curse of sin&mdash;a sample of what the whole earth would have become had man but fulfilled the Creator&apos;s glorious plan.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">1<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"PP 62.1\" data-link=\"84.211\">Patriarchs and Prophets, 62</span>.</span></a></sup>",
