    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "<strong>The United Family of Heaven and Earth</strong>&mdash;There the redeemed shall &ldquo;know, even as also they are known.&rdquo; The loves and sympathies which God Himself has planted in the soul shall there find truest and sweetest exercise. The pure communion with holy beings, the harmonious social life with the blessed angels and with the faithful ones of all ages who have washed their robes and made them white in the blood of the Lamb, the sacred ties that bind together &ldquo;the whole family in heaven and earth&rdquo;&mdash;these help to constitute the happiness of the redeemed.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">9<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"GC 677.1\" data-link=\"132.3058\">The Great Controversy, 677</span>.</span></a></sup>",
