    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "From that scene of heavenly joy [the ascension of Christ] there comes back to us on earth the echo of Christ&apos;s own wonderful words, &ldquo;I ascend unto My Father, and your Father; and to My God, and your God.&rdquo; The family of heaven and the family of earth are one. For us our Lord ascended, and for us He lives. &ldquo;Wherefore He is able also to save them to the uttermost that come unto God by Him, seeing He ever liveth to make intercession for them.&rdquo;<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">11<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"DA 835.2\" data-link=\"130.4114\">The Desire of Ages, 835</span>.</span></a></sup>",
