    "content": "<strong>Though Delayed, the Promise Is Sure</strong>&mdash;Long have we waited for our Saviour&apos;s return. But none the less sure is the promise. Soon we shall be in our promised home. There Jesus will lead us beside the living stream flowing from the throne of God and will explain to us the dark providences through which on this earth He brought us in order to perfect our characters. There we <span class=\"page-break\" data-page=\"545\"></span> shall behold with undimmed vision the beauties of Eden restored. Casting at the feet of the Redeemer the crowns that He has placed on our heads and touching our golden harps, we shall fill all heaven with praise to Him that sitteth on the throne.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">12<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"8T 254.1\" data-link=\"112.1450\">Testimonies for the Church 8:254</span>.</span></a></sup>",
