    "refcode_long": "The Adventist Home, p. 545.1 (Ellen Gould White)",
    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "Let all that is beautiful in our earthly home remind us of the crystal river and green fields, the waving trees and the living fountains, the shining city and the white-robed singers, of our heavenly home&mdash;that world of beauty which no artist can picture, no mortal tongue describe. &ldquo;Eye hath not seen, nor ear heard, neither have entered into the heart of man, the things which God hath prepared for them that love Him.&rdquo;<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">13<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"RH 7-11-1882\" data-link=\"821.4439\">The Review and Herald, July 11, 1882</span>.</span></a></sup>",
